verses.roman:
ei-mata saṅkhyātīta caitanya-bhakta-gaṇa
diṅmātra likhi, samyak nā yāya kathana

synonyms: ei-mata—in this way; saṅkhyā-atīta—innumerable; caitanya-bhakta-gaṇa—devotees of Lord Caitanya; diṅ-mātra—only a fractional part; likhi—I write; samyak—full; nā—cannot; yāya—be possible; kathana—to explain.
translation: I list in this way only a portion of the innumerable devotees of Lord Caitanya. To describe them all fully is not possible.
